{"metadata":{"externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot10ConfigFileC","roleHeading":"Class","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"class","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}],"title":"ConfigFile","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ConfigFile","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"ConfigFile"}]},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/configfile"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConfigFile","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Helper class to handle INI-style files."}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"ConfigFile","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This helper class can be used to store "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Variant","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" values on the filesystem using INI-style formatting. The stored values are identified by a section and a key:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The stored data can be saved to or parsed from a file, though ConfigFile objects can also be used directly without accessing the filesystem."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The following example shows how to create a simple ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/ConfigFile","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and save it on disc:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows how the above file could be loaded:"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Any operation that mutates the ConfigFile such as "},{"identifier